cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.MG, cs.SY. 

This paper deals with geometric combinatorics, specifically the problem of finding joints in a set of lines in $\reals^d$. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses algebraic techniques, which could potentially place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the maximum possible number of joints, which could be considered a problem in extremal combinatorics, placing it in cs.MG (Mathematical Physics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
